# ClickHouse SQL Conventions

## Database: `otel`

## Core Tables

| Table | Engine | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|
| `otel_traces` | MergeTree | Spans — TraceId, SpanId, SpanName, Duration, SpanAttributes, ResourceAttributes |
| `otel_logs` | MergeTree | Logs — TraceId, Body, SeverityText, LogAttributes, ResourceAttributes |
| `otel_metrics_gauge` | MergeTree | Gauge metrics — MetricName, Value, Attributes, ResourceAttributes |
| `stack_trace_events` | MergeTree | Symbolicated + grouped stack traces |

## Key Columns in `otel_traces`

`TraceId`, `SpanId`, `ParentSpanId`, `SpanName`, `SpanKind`, `ServiceName`, `Duration` (nanoseconds), `StatusCode`, `StatusMessage`, `SpanAttributes` (Map), `ResourceAttributes` (Map), `Timestamp` (DateTime64)

## Materialized Columns

These columns are extracted from Map attributes at insert time. **Always use these instead of accessing the Map columns directly** — they are faster and indexed.

| Column | Source Key | Source Map | Available In |
|--------|-----------|------------|--------------|
| `ProjectId` | `project.id` | ResourceAttributes | all tables |
| `PulseType` | `pulse.type` | SpanAttributes/LogAttributes | all tables |
| `SessionId` | `session.id` | SpanAttributes/LogAttributes/Attributes | all tables |
| `AppVersion` | `app.build_name` | ResourceAttributes | all tables |
| `SDKVersion` | `rum.sdk.version` | ResourceAttributes | all tables |
| `Platform` | `os.name` | ResourceAttributes | all tables |
| `OsVersion` | `os.version` | ResourceAttributes | all tables |
| `GeoState` | `geo.region.iso_code` | SpanAttributes/LogAttributes/Attributes | all tables |
| `GeoCountry` | `geo.country.iso_code` | SpanAttributes/LogAttributes/Attributes | all tables |
| `DeviceModel` | `device.model.name` | ResourceAttributes | all tables |
| `NetworkProvider` | `network.carrier.name` | SpanAttributes/LogAttributes/Attributes | all tables |
| `UserId` | `user.id` | SpanAttributes/LogAttributes/Attributes | all tables |

`otel_traces` also has a deprecated `SpanType` column (same source as `PulseType`).

## ORDER BY Keys

All tables start their ORDER BY with `ProjectId` for multi-tenant isolation:

| Table | ORDER BY |
|-------|----------|
| `otel_traces` | `(ProjectId, ServiceName, PulseType, SpanName, Timestamp)` |
| `otel_logs` | `(ProjectId, ServiceName, PulseType, EventName, SeverityText, toUnixTimestamp(Timestamp), TraceId)` |
| `otel_metrics_gauge` | `(ProjectId, ServiceName, MetricName, Attributes, toUnixTimestamp64Nano(TimeUnix))` |
| `stack_trace_events` | `(ProjectId, GroupId, ExceptionType, toUnixTimestamp(Timestamp))` |

## `stack_trace_events` Key Columns

`Timestamp`, `TraceId`, `SpanId`, `GroupId`, `Fingerprint`, `ExceptionType`, `ExceptionMessage`, `ExceptionStackTrace`, `Title`, `ScreenName`, `Interactions`, `Platform`, `AppVersion`, `OsVersion`, `DeviceModel`, `ResourceAttributes`, `LogAttributes`, `ProjectId`, `PulseType`

## Pulse-Specific Span Attributes

Accessed via `SpanAttributes['key']` (for traces) or `LogAttributes['key']` (for logs):
- `pulse.type`, `pulse.interaction.name`, `screen.name`
- `app.build_name` (→ `AppVersion`), `os.name` (→ `Platform`), `device.model.name` (→ `DeviceModel`)

## Multi-Tenant Access (Row-Level Security)

Queries must use the ClickHouse tenant user for project-scoped data access. Credentials are in `deploy/.env`:
- User: `OTEL_CLICKHOUSE_USER` (default: `pulse_user`)
- Password: `OTEL_CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD` (default: `pulse_password`)

The tenant user has row-level policies that filter by `ProjectId`, so queries automatically return only data for the authenticated project.

## Schema Conventions

- Use `MergeTree` engine with `ORDER BY` tuples for efficient range queries
- Partition by date (or `(ProjectId, date)` in replicated setup) for time-series data
- `DateTime64(9)` for nanosecond timestamps
- Map columns for flexible attributes
- `LowCardinality(String)` for low-cardinality materialized columns

## Query Rules

- Always include time-range filter on `Timestamp`
- Use `LIMIT` on all queries
- Prefer `toDateTime64()` for timestamp comparisons
- Use materialized columns (e.g., `Platform`, `AppVersion`) over Map access
- Use the tenant user for all queries to enforce project isolation
